# TESAIoT firmware and Bitstream (off `t3d-extension`)

The **host** implementation and docs live under this repo (`t3d-extension` / `src/bitstream`). For **firmware truth** (what fields mean, counters, encoders, task flow), the authoritative sources are in the **TESAIoT** workspace on this machine—**not** vendored inside `ternion-t3d`.

When the user (or the task) mentions **Protocol**, **Bitstream**, or **firmware behavior** and the answer is not fully specified in `src/bitstream` or the webview, **check or reference** these locations:

| Role | Path |
|------|------|
| **Main firmware** | `D:\CODE\2026\TESAIoT_PSoC_Edge_Workspace\TESAIoT_Firmware` |
| **Library** | `D:\CODE\2026\TESAIoT_PSoC_Edge_Workspace\TESAIoT_Library` |
| **Bitstream (firmware module)** | `D:\CODE\2026\TESAIoT_PSoC_Edge_Workspace\TESAIoT_Firmware\proj_cm55\src\bitstream` |
| **Bitstream Simulator (host virtual MCU)** | `D:\CODE\2026\ternion-t3d\bitstream-simulator` — see **`bitstream-simulator-app-path.mdc`** |

## Agent behavior

1. Prefer **`proj_cm55\src\bitstream`** for payload layout, sensor publish logic, and counters versus **`src/bitstream`** (host) for decode/UI parity.
2. Use **`TESAIoT_Library`** when shared drivers/types cross projects.
3. If those folders are outside the current Cursor workspace, **say so** and use terminal/read tools with **absolute paths** when the environment allows, or ask the user to add the TESAIoT folder to the workspace for direct file reads.

## Firmware Bitstream portability (non-negotiable)

When implementing or refactoring firmware Bitstream code under
`D:\CODE\2026\TESAIoT_PSoC_Edge_Workspace\TESAIoT_Firmware\proj_cm55\src\bitstream`:

- **Isolation requirement**: Treat Bitstream as a **copyable module**. Do **not** include headers from other firmware modules/services (Wi‑Fi, diagnostics, UI, transport, app-level code) inside the protocol core and shared Bitstream sources.
- **Ports-only integration**: All project-specific wiring must go through the **protocol port layer** under:
  - `D:\CODE\2026\TESAIoT_PSoC_Edge_Workspace\TESAIoT_Firmware\proj_cm55\src\bitstream\protocol\port\include`
- **Copy-to-other-project goal**: A user must be able to copy the entire `proj_cm55\src\bitstream` folder into another firmware project and have it work by editing **only** the protocol port files (and their adapter implementations) without touching protocol logic, encoders/decoders, or channel handlers.

If a change would violate this, restructure it behind a port API (or a thin adapter owned by the target module) instead of adding new cross-module includes to Bitstream.

## Communication

Per project language rules, explain in **Thai and/or English** only.
